{"info": {"author": "Ramon Brandt", "author_email": "devramon22@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# Basic LDAP3\n\nBasic LDAP is a small package that uses the ldap3 library. It can be used to authenticate a user against an LDAP server and can check whether the users is in a specific group. In addition it is possible to get user attributes if the authentication is successful.\n\n## Basic example\n\n### Import basicldap and define the server\n```python\nfrom basicldap import Ldap\n\nLDAP_HOST = 'ldap.server.com'\nLDAP_BASE_DN = 'DC=example,DC=com'\n\nconn = Ldap(LDAP_HOST, LDAP_BASE_DN)\n\n# Using SSL\nssl = {\"port\": 636, \"use_ssl\": True}\nconn = Ldap(LDAP_HOST, LDAP_BASE_DN, ldap3_args=ssl)\n```\n### Authenticate the user\n```python\nconn.authenticate(user_name, password)\n```\n\n### Get user attributes (requires successful authentication)\n```python\n# To get all attributes\nconn.get_attributes()\n\n# To get specific attributes\nconn.get_attributes(['mail', 'cn])\n```", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "basicldap3", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/basicldap3/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/basicldap3/", "project_urls": null, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/basicldap3/0.1.2/", "requires_dist": ["ldap3 (>=2.6.1,<3.0.0)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "summary": "Provides basic authentication using the ldap3 library", "version": "0.1.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Basic LDAP3</h1>\n<p>Basic LDAP is a small package that uses the ldap3 library. It can be used to authenticate a user against an LDAP server and can check whether the users is in a specific group. In addition it is possible to get user attributes if the authentication is successful.</p>\n<h2>Basic example</h2>\n<h3>Import basicldap and define the server</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">basicldap</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Ldap</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">LDAP_HOST</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'ldap.server.com'</span>\n<span class=\"n\">LDAP_BASE_DN</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'DC=example,DC=com'</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">conn</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Ldap</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LDAP_HOST</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">LDAP_BASE_DN</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Using SSL</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ssl</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"s2\">\"port\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">636</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"use_ssl\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">conn</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Ldap</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LDAP_HOST</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">LDAP_BASE_DN</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">ldap3_args</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">ssl</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h3>Authenticate the user</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">conn</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">user_name</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">password</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h3>Get user attributes (requires successful authentication)</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># To get all attributes</span>\n<span class=\"n\">conn</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_attributes</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># To get specific attributes</span>\n<span class=\"n\">conn</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_attributes</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"s1\">'mail'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'cn])</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6702548, "releases": {"0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "109e4600c6f8b134da261a3174d62976", "sha256": "af5f12044de8fbd0ae0559b4eb4fe08114ac38a624e31f8a485d437266fcb09c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "basicldap3-0.1.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "109e4600c6f8b134da261a3174d62976", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 2579, "upload_time": "2020-02-25T11:58:17", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-25T11:58:17.894848Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/8b/cc/a7db553685406a340b6b8d47c5de163fd2994d41f7c0030070654e47e32e/basicldap3-0.1.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "7ad54891ef5c1b2a35b40880e35e62a2", "sha256": "9da9670a7a74f7e0bde5edf1012eb565f7a45ac2a22af337ef44c0d0e6a091e5"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "basicldap3-0.1.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "7ad54891ef5c1b2a35b40880e35e62a2", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 2661, "upload_time": "2020-02-25T11:58:19", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-25T11:58:19.551337Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/45/7d/7bba15385685209e13baf45c662df5151ff121313cb100662402ca1cad87/basicldap3-0.1.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "888cff9aef5608568f3aa8140417b15d", "sha256": "cc846a2fbe9e19ab9d81869033f9e827016f59c77d3f52a4881aee1a66b5edd1"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "bas